caption: Had a wonderful dinner with a special friend.  Outstanding service, food, and atmosphere.  There were only two of us, but we were kindly given a four-top upon request.  We enjoyed every dish, as well as an outstanding Brunello.  The host …

Really happy that I stumbled across this place!! The restaurant has a very cozy atmosphere to it, and the staff are attentive and professional. I had a great and fairly-priced glass of Chianti, as well as the gnocchi, which were absolutely to die for!! This really is simple food, made very well. Grazie!
Definitely a place I look forward to visit again! Both the food and the service were superb. I wish you guys the best during these tough times.
Amazing food and amazing service. Honestly the best Italian food I’ve had in my life. I will come back here for years to come!
Best Gnocchi in the World!

This is our favorite restaurant in San Francisco.  A fabulous selection of pastas and perfectly prepared veal dishes.  Their takeout portions are enormous.  You just can’t go wrong with this place. We keep coming back again and again and …

Perfect neighborhood place for COVID Time Dining with outdoor tables. We shared arugula and burrata, Sangiovese, and each ordered pasta from the house. The food quickly came out and the waiting workers were polite, attentive and wearing masks. Once again, I'll be back!

Authentic northern Italian food in the heart of the City!  Hand made, fresh pastas (gnocchi, ravioli, fettuccine...) and great main dishes like Saltimbocca di Pollo, plus tiramisu - you can't go wrong.  Currently offering takeout only (end of 2020) - added to the takeout rotation.

Great little neighborhood find. Had the breaded sardines and bresaola and a couple of glasses of wine. Great service, delicious food, neat little spot. Loved everything about it, especially the service which was extremely attentive. Highly recommend!

What a gem of a place !  The food here is pretty much all great . Aldo makes sure to get the freshest fish and food for the dishes and it certainly shows . The bolognese with fettuccine was SO good I came from Oakland a week later to have …

The service is amazing and the food is outstanding!  Butternut squash ravioli, Burrata and arugula salad and most importantly the delicious and perfectly cooked Veal chop!  Aldo is a gracious and welcoming owner and Susannah is on top of everything and delightfully charming. If you want fantastic Italian food, this is the place.
20 years later, still the same high quality and taste. Aldo is the best.

Came here unexpectedly but it turned out quite a good job. We were recommended a grilled Calamari as an appetizer. It was nicely grilled and very soft. And we had porcini mushroom pasta and seafood linguine. Everything was greatly balanced …
One of the best in area! Great service, Great Food. Great location. Wine list to die for.

Fabulous food, well priced, attentive service and the outdoor seating was nice because the street was quiet. I had the fettuccine puttanesca which they did with anchovies as well as the usual capers and olives. The fettucine  itself was excellent. The best experience that I have had dining since outdoor dining began.

Our first time in SF. We where craving Italian food, so I found this place 4 min away from our hotel, omg may I say it's been the best place we've been to here in SF we order something that wasn't in the menu, alfredo with linguini, it was delicious, the gentleman's were soo polite and attentive, the tiramisu was very good too
Always great to visit this amazing place. Great service and great food! Outside patio available, staff wears masks and gloves too. They also have take out and delivery options.
Small intimate place.  Good food and great service.
Great Food in a local neighborhood restaurant. Quaint and authentic.

One of my favorite Italian restaurants in the City, Ristorante Milano serves authentic northern Italian food using fresh, local ingredients. It has a very small dining room, attentive staff, and delicious food. I love their house-made pasta dishes, of which my favorite is their Linguine ai Frutti di Mare.
Food ok.
Best Italian is SF

Best Italian in the city. Simple, straightforward dishes that are otherworldly.  Gnocci that are buttery smooth Mushroom and sausage pasta with out of this world creaminess 🤤 Tira misu was top notch Fantastic 🍷 Even the rosemary 🍞 to start was special
Cutest little hidden San Francisco gem! Gnocchi was incredible! Wine is very fair priced. Service was personalized and lovely! Can’t wait to come back
kinda like the milano cookie
Fabulous food, service, and location.

In a city of exquisite Italian cuisine, Milano stands out as an authentic dining experience, expertly prepared food, great wine list and wine specials served in a friendly family restaurant atmosphere with just the right touch of elegance
I like the pasta because the sause is wonderful.
Great food. Great service
Great neighborhood restaurant. Wonderful food. Ask for the linguini and truffle pasta. It's only available during truffle season, which is October to January. Not usually on the menu. You'll love it.
italian food... excellent. Very appetizing. The staff was very sociable and kind. This place has a nice feel to it.
Superb as usual. Had a great dinner tonight.
All the dishes were very good.
The lasagna is soft, delicate and my favourite!

I love this restaurant! I have been going for years and has always had the best and most affordable Italian food in my area. And they deliver too! Great place to go if it's just 2 people b/c you can share and INDIVIDUAL portion side and FREE garlic balls! Yum!
Good service, food is ok, nothing great. Very, very expensive. If you expect real Italian food you'll be disappointed.
Excellent as usual.  A must do when visiting SF.
Good Italian fare. Liked the canneli bean salad with grilled squid and the gnocchi.
Fantastic find for a quick bite, no crowds - pure Italy.  Cucina perfetta!

Outstanding meal off the beaten path.   This place is worth the effort.  I highly recommend the veal chop and the Seafood risotto.  The fettuccine al Mare was also very good as was the Rigatoni.  Friendly and simply very good.  Bring your family and friends.
One of the best Italian restaurant in the area.
Great food, very fresh!
Loved the cozy place and the tasty food.
Hidden gem of SF: small and cozy. Food is great and the service is very attentive.

A gem of an authentic Milan ristorante that is not on the SF tourist parade. Small. quaint and personal. Service is family-like...waiters, chefs and bus boys alike. Food was all around great. Solid neighborhood joint like you find in New York and Chicago.
If you're looking for great Italian dining experience you just found it. Service  quality and consistency makes this very charmy restaurant a very special place.
The food and wine are great and the hosts are friendly.
Cosy great food & atmosphere, friendly people
High quality fresh pasta

Small neighborhood restaurant. The food here is rich and filling. The gnocchi was buttery and tasted wonderful. Veggie lentil soup was alright. The homemade tiramasu was rich. The service was attentive and friendly.

Just stopped with my husband for dinner. We had a bottle of the California Sauvignon Blanc, it was very fruity and tasty.  We shared the pear salad, nice contrast with bitter greens, pears, and goat cheese. We also shared their ravioli of …
Great service, good food.
The bread was delicious! I got the chestnut stuffed ravioli tasted fresh!
Best Italian restaurant I've been to in the bay area. Tonnarelli is a must!
Excellent Italian restaurant with fresh pasta and great wine list. Small, quaint restaurant with attentive staff.
Highly recommended, excellent service, delicious, well presented dishes in a cosy and romantic setting.
The food there was AMAZING and the Customer service was great. The place is small and Quaint so if you have a large party, call and make a reservation before hand.
I love this place. Great pasta. Quiet, intimate. The best tonnarelli in town.
Great cute little Italian restaurant with awesome appetizers and equally great entrees! And it’s ideal for dates.
Wonderful neighborhood restaurant with excellent food. Small and quiet.

Great service,  great food.  I had the gnocchi and you could tell they were home made.  It was late at night on a Wednesday and you could tell they were trying to close down but my glass was never out of water and the waiter was very attentive.
Hands down best Italian restaurant in San Francisco ever 😋👍

Great family place with authentic Italian cuisine. Wide selection of Italian and California wines. Highly recommended to check this place out.
Amazing atmosphere, amazing food. Our favorite place to eat when we come to the city. Very boutique type of restaurant.
Not the best Italian restaurant in San Francisco but had a very good meal which I enjoyed. Good service and fair price. Would go again
Nice and lovely place.
Authentic Italian with super cozy atmosphere
Best Italian food outside of Italy you will ever have
Warm and friendly atmosphere with great tasting food at a reasonable price. Highly recommend

Great food!! Nice owners!!
Great Italian fare with incredible daily specials.
Awesome restaurant in SF's best neighborhood
Authentic, or so it seemed.    Very good veal.   Sweet fresh tomato sauce on homemade pasta.  Good wine.  Priced right.  Maurizzio was good host.

Wonderful Italian food, attentive service, family owned business.  Warm and cozy place. Great price $$$ for fantastic food.
Dine here every time I'm in the city!
Terrific food and service. Italian cooking at its best.

Ate here during a weekend away with friends. Small, attractive restaurant with a nice atmosphere. The service was very attentive. The food was excellent. I had their homemade gnocchi and it was so good, perfectly sauced, and tasted like …
A wonderful intimate family owned Italian Restaurant. I love it here.

Wonderful service.  We loved our meal wine and dessert.  The best tables are way in the back on a mezzanine - almost private.  Go early and snag one of those back tables.   I had the seafood risotto and enjoyed it immensely.  A nice rose' went nicely. We are going back again for sure its an easy walk from Russian hill.
Delicious pasta
Excellent food and srvice.  Very small restauant.  Parking is a challenge.
A neighborhood favorite of mine, terrific food (the risottos are always a knockout!), and great service.
Veal saltamboca was excellent
Rather jammed into a small space but the food is nice and you can walk to Union Square after dinner.

Great home made Italian food.  Pasta is all freshly made on site.  The fish was sublime and the pasta perfect.  Wine selection was fair and our waitress was actually Italian and very attentive.  Highly recommend this place
Always beyond expectations!
Gnocchi was amazing!!! Domiano the host was fabulous. The food was really delicious, but the noise was DEAFENING! I was wincing in pain and had to get my meal to go.
Good food, good service! What more do you want. Authentic Italian food, this is a great place to have a date at any stage of a relationship! ;)
This is one of my favorite date spots! The fresh pasta is really good and you know it's a gem because it's hidden away from all of the touristy stuff!
Good service, good food, good wine :)
Ask for Aldo. The most amazing host ever.
Authentic upmarket-family-style Italian restaurant, with a buzz; good food; and friendly staff.  Good wine list; generous portions.

Dinner at Ristorante Milano was one of the most authentic Italian meal experiences I've had in San Francisco. Every dish was cooked perfectly, and the pastas tasted fresh. Servers were cheerful; ours explained the journey of the truffle from Italy as she was grating shavings of it into my pasta!
Excellent Italian food, very friendly staff, good atmosphere
Great service fantastic food and fine wine

The BEST Italian in the entire City! Awesome place! Best kept little secret, and it is better than my grandma's cooking from the old country! And hand made pasta and ice cream. Can't get better than that!
We had an awful service and dining experience; from long waits on appetizers and entrées to an  uncouth staff, I will not recommend an plan on going back.

Small, cozy restaurant with good but not particularly memorable food.
Great food, ambience, and service. Prosciutto appetizer plate is huge. Great pastas. Woild come again
Great food and staff attention. Bit loud early in the evening but was not impeding conversations.
great service, good food.. but way too expensive for such small portions

I went here for a friend's birthday dinner a few weeks ago. We had a long, private table at the front of the restaurant with windows overlooking the street. They did a great job accommodating our ~10 person group.  For an appetizer, the …
A superior restaurant. The food and service are excellent.
good Italian food cooked by an Italian family.  Order the lasagne ahead-excellent!

Get a reservation because it's typically full. Food is yummy; seems authentic and the service is generally great except that they make you wait at the front door for what seems like ever until they come to greet you.
A taste of Rome in SF...best gnocchi in SF.
Order the lasagna (available on the weekends) and a glass of the Valpolicella. If they have them, a profiterole for dessert. Delicious food, attentive and friendly wait staff.

The food is hit or miss at Milano.  I loved the squash ravioli, too bad we ordered that as an app.  My lasagna was so-so at best.  My wife had a great seafood risotto.  So 2/3 is not bad.  I'm still looking for that great Italian place in sf.
